commentTextItems.html: and that's it, short ball cut away past point to give the Scots a very comprehensive win

commentPostTextItems.html: So another poor performance by The Netherlands but plenty of positives for Scotland who now lead the table, the highlights of today's play were John Blain's 5-wicket haul and a lovely innings from the skipper, who finished unbeaten on 54

Tomorrow is a rest day in the Championships but do join us on Thursday for the decider between Scotland and Ireland. Again we start at 10.45am in Clontarf, that's all from me, Chris Busby, for today. Cheers!

commentTextItems.html: driven through midwicket, excellent running brings two runs
probably the best shot of the day, driven on the up straight back past the bowler
cut to third man on the back foot for four

lovely bit of timing as Watson clips a full ball through midwicket. It was a no ball as well
single taken as McCallum drives wide of mid off
not this time, another flighted ball and after a few skips down the wicket Watson hits through mid on for four
